## Database Standards

### Column Types

- `string` - Short text (max 255 characters)
- `text` - Long text (articles, descriptions)
- `integer` - Whole numbers, foreign keys
- `bigint` - Large integers
- `decimal` - Money, precise numbers (use `precision:` and `scale:`)
- `float` - Approximate numbers
- `boolean` - True/false
- `date` - Date only
- `datetime` - Date and time
- `time` - Time only
- `json` - JSON data (PostgreSQL/MySQL)
- `jsonb` - Binary JSON (PostgreSQL, faster queries)

### Indexing Strategy

```ruby
# Always add indexes for:
add_index :articles, :user_id              # Foreign keys (automatic with t.references)
add_index :articles, :status               # Frequently queried columns
add_index :articles, :slug, unique: true   # Unique columns
add_index :articles, [:user_id, :status]   # Composite indexes for multi-column queries
add_index :articles, :published_at         # Date/time columns used in queries
```

## Testing Standards

### Model Tests

```ruby
# test/models/article_test.rb

require "test_helper"

class ArticleTest < ActiveSupport::TestCase
  test "should not save article without title" do
    article = Article.new(body: "Content")
    assert_not article.save
    assert_includes article.errors[:title], "can't be blank"
  end
  
  test "title should be at least 5 characters" do
    article = Article.new(title: "Hi", body: "Content")
    assert_not article.valid?
    assert_includes article.errors[:title], "is too short"
  end
  
  test "publish! should set status and timestamp" do
    article = articles(:draft)
    article.publish!
    
    assert_equal "published", article.status
    assert_not_nil article.published_at
  end
  
  test "published scope returns only published articles" do
    published_count = Article.where(status: 'published').count
    assert_equal published_count, Article.published.count
  end
end
```

### Controller Tests

```ruby
# test/controllers/articles_controller_test.rb

require "test_helper"

class ArticlesControllerTest < ActionDispatch::IntegrationTest
  setup do
    @article = articles(:one)
  end
  
  test "should get index" do
    get articles_url
    assert_response :success
    assert_select "h1", "Articles"
  end
  
  test "should create article with valid params" do
    assert_difference("Article.count") do
      post articles_url, params: { 
        article: { title: "New Article", body: "Content goes here" * 10 }
      }
    end
    
    assert_redirected_to article_url(Article.last)
    follow_redirect!
    assert_select "h1", "New Article"
  end
  
  test "should not create article with invalid params" do
    assert_no_difference("Article.count") do
      post articles_url, params: { article: { title: "", body: "" } }
    end
    
    assert_response :unprocessable_entity
  end
end
```

### System Tests

```ruby
# test/system/articles_test.rb

require "application_system_test_case"

class ArticlesTest < ApplicationSystemTestCase
  test "creating an article" do
    visit articles_url
    click_on "New Article"
    
    fill_in "Title", with: "System Test Article"
    fill_in "Body", with: "This is a system test article with enough content"
    click_on "Create Article"
    
    assert_text "Article was successfully created"
    assert_text "System Test Article"
  end
  
  test "editing article with Turbo Frame" do
    article = articles(:one)
    visit article_url(article)
    
    click_on "Edit"
    fill_in "Title", with: "Updated Title"
    click_on "Update Article"
    
    # Turbo Frame should update without full page reload
    assert_text "Updated Title"
    assert_no_text "Article was successfully updated" # No flash since Turbo Frame
  end
end
```

**Testing Rules**:
- Test all model validations
- Test all model public methods
- Test critical controller actions (create, update, destroy)
- Test important user flows with system tests
- Run tests frequently: `rails test`
- Keep tests fast (use fixtures, avoid external calls)

## Rails 8 Authentication

```bash
# Generate authentication system
rails generate authentication
```

**Generated Files**:
- `app/models/user.rb` - User model with `has_secure_password`
- `app/models/session.rb` - Session model for tracking
- `app/controllers/sessions_controller.rb` - Login/logout
- `app/controllers/passwords_controller.rb` - Password reset
- `app/views/sessions/` - Login views
- `app/views/passwords/` - Password reset views
- Migration for users and sessions tables

**Usage**:
```ruby
# app/controllers/application_controller.rb
class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base
  before_action :require_authentication
  
  private
  
  def require_authentication
    redirect_to sign_in_path unless authenticated?
  end
  
  def authenticated?
    Current.user.present?
  end
end
```

## Code Quality Rules

### DRY Principle

```ruby
# Bad: Repetition
class ArticlesController
  def show
    redirect_to login_path unless current_user
  end
end

class CommentsController
  def create
    redirect_to login_path unless current_user
  end
end

# Good: Extract to parent
class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base
  before_action :require_login
  
  private
  def require_login
    redirect_to login_path unless current_user
  end
end
```

### KISS Principle

```ruby
# Bad: Overly complex
def formatted_date
  if published_at.present?
    if published_at > 1.year.ago
      published_at.strftime("%B %d, %Y")
    else
      published_at.strftime("%Y")
    end
  else
    "Draft"
  end
end

# Good: Simple and clear
def formatted_date
  return "Draft" unless published_at
  published_at > 1.year.ago ? published_at.strftime("%B %d, %Y") : published_at.year
end
```

### Semantic HTML

```erb
