    <div>Article Title</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### ARIA Labels

```erb
<!-- Navigation -->
<nav aria-label="Main navigation" id="main-navigation">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/" id="nav-home-link">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- Forms -->
<form role="search" aria-label="Search articles" id="article-search-form">
  <label for="search-input" class="sr-only">Search</label>
  <input id="search-input" type="search" placeholder="Search...">
  <button type="submit" aria-label="Submit search" id="search-submit-button">
    <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- icon --></svg>
  </button>
</form>

<!-- Icon-only buttons -->
<button type="button" aria-label="Close modal" id="modal-close-button">
  <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
</button>
```

### Keyboard Navigation

```erb
<!-- Good: Native button (keyboard accessible) -->
<button type="button" id="user-menu-button">Menu</button>

<!-- If using non-button (avoid): -->
<div role="button" 
     tabindex="0" 
     data-action="click->menu#toggle keydown->menu#handleKey"
     id="custom-menu-button">
  Menu
</div>
```

**Accessibility Rules**:
- All images need `alt` attributes
- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`)
- Ensure keyboard navigation works (test with Tab key)
- Use `<label>` for all form inputs
- Provide ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- Use `.sr-only` class for screen reader only text
- Ensure color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text)

## Performance Guidelines

### Database Optimization

```ruby
# Bad: N+1 query
@articles = Article.all
@articles.each do |article|
  article.user.name  # Separate query for each article!
end

# Good: Eager loading
@articles = Article.includes(:user).all
@articles.each do |article|
  article.user.name  # No additional queries
end

# Good: Scoped queries with limits
@recent_articles = Article.published.recent.limit(10)
```

**Query Rules**:
- Always use `includes()` when accessing associations
- Use `limit()` for paginated results
- Use `select()` to load only needed columns
- Add indexes for frequently queried columns

### Caching with Solid Cache

```ruby
# Fragment caching in views
<% cache @article do %>
  <%= render @article %>
<% end %>

# Russian Doll caching
<% cache ['articles', @articles.maximum(:updated_at)] do %>
  <%= render @articles %>
<% end %>
```

